cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) as it deals with abstractive summarization of scientific articles. Additionally, the use of sequence to sequence models and gated recurrent units are common techniques in NLP research. 

The paper may also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a new model architecture for the encoder-decoder setting. 

Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is another likely sub-category as the paper deals with improving the ability of seq2seq models to capture compositionalities better. 

Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is a possible sub-category as summarization is a common task in IR research. 

Finally, Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) is a possible sub-category as the proposed model uses gated recurrent units, which are a type of neural network architecture.
